"'''God, Country and My Baby'''" is a song written by John Dolan and Chico Holiday. It was originally released by Holiday on the New Phoenix label in September 1961<ref>[https://www.45cat.com/record/6190 Chico Holiday - God, Country and My Baby / Fools - New Phoenix - USA - 6190]</ref> and later by [[Johnny Burnette]] in October of 1961. Burnette's version reached #18 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] in 1961.<ref>[http://www.musicvf.com/song.php?title=God%2C+Country+and+My+Baby+by+Johnny+Burnette&id=22867 Johnny Burnette, "God, Country and My Baby" Chart Position] Retrieved April 30, 2014</ref> The song appeared on his 1962 album, ''Johnny Burnette's Hits and Other Favorites''.<ref>[http://www.discogs.com/Johnny-Burnette-Johnny-Burnettes-Hits-And-Other-Favorites/release/5163210 Johnny Burnette, ''Johnny Burnette's Hits and Other Favorites''] Retrieved April 30, 2014</ref>

The song was produced by [[Snuff Garrett]].  [[Johnny Mann|The Johnny Mann Singers]] are featured on the song.<ref>[http://www.45cat.com/record/f55379 Johnny Burnette, "God, Country and My Baby" single release] Retrieved April 30, 2014</ref>

